segment.source: How to Open a Sequenced Application Using the Command Line
segment.target: How to Open a Sequenced Application Using the Command Line

segment.source: You can open virtual application packages using the command line.
segment.target: You can open virtual application packages using the command line.

segment.source: You must run the cmd prompt as an administrator.
segment.target: You must run the cmd prompt as an administrator.

segment.source: Use the following procedure to open sequenced application packages using the command line
segment.target: Use the following procedure to open sequenced application packages using the command line

segment.source: To open a sequenced application using the command line
segment.target: To open a sequenced application using the command line

segment.source: To open the command prompt, click Start, and select Run, type cmd, and click OK.
segment.target: To open the command prompt, click Start, and select Run, type cmd, and click OK.

segment.source: At a command prompt, type cd and specify the path to the directory where the Sequencer is installed and then press Enter.
segment.target: At a command prompt, type cd and specify the path to the directory where the Sequencer is installed and then press Enter.

segment.source: At the command prompt, type the following command, replacing the italicized text with your values:
segment.target: At the command prompt, type the following command, replacing the italicized text with your values:

segment.source: SFTSequencer /OPEN:”specifies the .sprj file to open"
segment.target: SFTSequencer /OPEN:”specifies the .sprj file to open"

segment.source: Press Enter.
segment.target: Press Enter.

segment.source: You can also specify the following optional parameters.
segment.target: You can also specify the following optional parameters.

segment.source: At the command prompt, type the following commands, replacing the italicized text with your values:
segment.target: At the command prompt, type the following commands, replacing the italicized text with your values:

segment.source: /PACKAGENAME:"specifies the package name"
segment.target: /PACKAGENAME:"specifies the package name"

segment.source: /MSI - specifies generating an associated Microsoft Windows Installer.
segment.target: /MSI - specifies generating an associated Microsoft Windows Installer.

segment.source: /COMPRESS – specifies if the package will be compressed.
segment.target: /COMPRESS – specifies if the package will be compressed.

segment.source: By default, packages are not compressed.
segment.target: By default, packages are not compressed.

segment.source: Press Enter.
segment.target: Press Enter.

segment.source: Note
segment.target: Note

segment.source: If the installer or Windows Installer package has a graphical user interface, it will be displayed after you specify the command-line parameters.
segment.target: If the installer or Windows Installer package has a graphical user interface, it will be displayed after you specify the command-line parameters.
